cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on learning policies for robotic assembly. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as the proposed method involves using visual input to learn shape descriptors for object-to-placement correspondences. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper proposes a machine learning approach to learn effective pick and place strategies. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also relevant as the paper proposes a self-supervised data-collection pipeline to obtain training data for the model. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as the paper involves designing a real-world system for assembly tasks.
